Westwood Junior High School
September 8 at 10:05 AM ·

Due to the number of ticket request and sells, we will be moving the remaining Junior High volleyball games to the High school gym. The seating capacity at the high school is 225 for the home stands and 125 for visitors.

Because of the JH homecoming football game, on Thursday, September 10th ONLY, we will be utilizing both the JH and HS gyms. The games are as followed:

JH gym: 7th/8th Combo team @ 4:00 p.m.
7th grade A @ 4:30 p.m.

HS gym: 8th grade A @ 4:30 p.m.

All other games will be played on Monday nights at 4:30, 5:00, and 6:00 p.m.

We understand this is a big change but we want to ensure that our athletes are able to participate in all of their extracurricular activities. If you have any questions, feel free to email Coach Harris at dharris@westwoodisd.net.

post_text:
💥Breakfast with Champions Mentor Program 💥

The number one social issue we have in our society is fatherless homes. Even homes with a dad who lives there sometimes does not have an active role with their children. Studies show the average father spends 2.5 minutes per day in ‘meaningful conversation’ with their children….amazing!!

We must do what we can to help fill the void. Our coaches will be great role models, but we also get other men involved using our Breakfast with Champions program.

HOW IT WORKS..
Each mentor ‘adopts’ a player for the season.
Program is on Friday mornings at 7:30.
7:30 – highlight video from previous week
7:35 – introduce Guest speaker
7:50 – announce award winners from previous week
7:55 – talk about upcoming game

If interested email Coach Bishop rdbishop@westwoodisd.net

post_text:
Technology device handout will be held at the High School for Primary and Elementary families who chose Home-Base Learning this Wednesday, August 12th from 4:30 to 6:30 pm.

On August 13th from 4:30 to 6:30 pm, we will hold another device handout at the High School for Junior High and High School students who chose Home-Base Learning.

Registration is required prior to receiving a device. If you have not registered, please so do so by going to https://www.westwoodisd.net/apps/pages/online-registration can completing the registration process

The handout process is designed so you don't have to leave your car. Please follow the map for guidance on the drive-thru the process.

Upon entering the High School entrance, you will stop at the registration checkpoint to verify your student is registered to attend. Once verified, you will drive to the device pickup zone in front of the building. There you will be issued a technology device.

Attention WISD parents and guardians, please complete the WISD Instructional Location Commitment Form for the 2020-2021 school year. Please fill out commitment form per student that attends Westwood ISD.

WISD Instructional Location Commitment Form: https://bit.ly/WISDCOMMITMENTFORM

Parents/guardians who do not have online access may come to the Westwood ISD Administration Office to complete the survey on Wednesday, August 5, 2020, through Friday, August 14, 2020, anytime between 8:30 AM to 3:30 PM.

post_text:
THANK YOU, Representative Cody Harris for speaking out on behalf of our community and kids by asking Commissioner Mike Morath to postpone STAAR testing. We are so grateful for your support.

Put education first, not standardized testing.
shared_text:
Cody Harris
July 9 at 8:03 PM ·

Today, I sent a letter to the Commissioner of the Texas Education Agency, Mike Morath, asking him to abandon his plans to reimplement STAAR testing next school year.

In an academic year when our kids are already going to be behind due to the state-wide shutdown, the last thing we need is for our teachers and students to be focusing time on how to pass the STAAR test.

2020-2021 School Supply List is now available! Please see the following link for your student's specific campus and grade level.

School Supply List: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/14B50L55iXpehqGCkcDoj3qq0xKk-3Nsk?usp=sharing

This year, WISD has partnered with Best In Class to bundle prepackaged school supplies per grade level as an option for parents. Your student's bundle will be delivered to their campus before school starts. Packages can be purchased at the following website: https://www.schoolsupplypacks.com/360-westwood-isd-palestine-texas

*Does not include backpack, school supplies only.

Note: Parents/guardians can still independently purchase their student's own school supplies per the list if they do not wish to utilize the prepackaged option.

If you would like to donate school supplies, select a grade level, and type DONATION in for the student's name.

If you have any questions, please contact ask@westwoodisd.net.

post_text:
P-EBT provides a one-time benefit of up to $285 per eligible child that families can use to purchase food. Eligible families that have children 5-18 years old and received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits. All other eligible families must apply to receive P-EBT benefits.

Thousands of families across Texas have applied for the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program. However, there are still many more students that are eligible for this program. On average, only 70% of eligible families in Texas have applied for P-EBT. The deadline to apply for P-EBT is Tuesday, June 30.

Application https://yourtexasbenefits.com/Learn/PEBT

Do you have questions about P-EBT?
For more information, please visit http://hhs.texas.gov/pebt (English) or http://hhs.texas.gov/es/pebt (Spanish) or contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220 Monday through Friday, 8:00 am – 6:00 pm.

Westwood High School
May 21 at 8:27 AM ·

🎓 High School Graduation Procedures and Dress Code 🎓

Seniors should arrive at the High School Field House by 6:30 PM to line up and be checked for dresscode.

Seniors should dress in their cap and gown attire.

BOYS are required to wear dress slacks or khaki pants, a white button down collared shirt, & dress shoes or shined boots in the colors of black, brown, or navy. Ties are not required, and NO earrings or other piercings will be worn.

GIRLS are required to wear a dress or dress slacks and dress top, with dress shoes or dress sandals in the colors of black, brown, or navy.

Any cap decorations must be school appropriate, cannot exceed 2 inches in height, and cannot hang over the edges of the cap. All graduating seniors will be required to wear masks.

After graduation, students will exit by the field house, and an area will be set up on both back corners of the field house for students to receive their official diplomas.

May 21 at 8:27 AM ·

🎓 High School Graduation Procedures and Dress Code 🎓

Seniors should arrive at the High School Field House by 6:30 PM to line up and be checked for dresscode.

Seniors should dress in their cap and gown attire.

BOYS are required to wear dress slacks or khaki pants, a white button down collared shirt, & dress shoes or shined boots in the colors of black, brown, or navy. Ties are not required, and NO earrings or other piercings will be worn.

GIRLS are required to wear a dress or dress slacks and dress top, with dress shoes or dress sandals in the colors of black, brown, or navy.

Any cap decorations must be school appropriate, cannot exceed 2 inches in height, and cannot hang over the edges of the cap. All graduating seniors will be required to wear masks.

After graduation, students will exit by the field house, and an area will be set up on both back corners of the field house for students to receive their official diplomas.

post_text:
Great News!!

While budget and supplies last, TEA will pay for up to 50 sets per grade level of the following materials for school districts and charter schools with over 50% of students classified as “economically disadvantaged.”

Publisher by Grade Level:
Pre-Kindergarten - Teaching Strategies
Kindergarten and First Grade - Learning Dynamics
First - Fifth Grade - Houghton Mifflin Harcourt

Please complete one form per child wishing to receive materials. A request for books to be shipped will be for the first 50 students in each grade level that sign up. Information put on this form will be sent directly to the publisher; therefore, accuracy is important.

Please sign up by Noon on Friday, May 22, 2020, so that list can be submitted for books while supplies last.

https://forms.gle/ENoWMemtWBiiTUHh8

Happy Earth Day!!

The theme for Earth Day 2020 is climate action. The enormous challenge — but also the vast opportunities — of action on climate change have distinguished the issue as the most pressing topic for the 50th anniversary.
Climate change represents the biggest challenge to the future of humanity and the life-support systems that make our world habitable.

Click the links below to check out these free National Education Association Earth Day Resources:

http://www.nea.org/tools/lessons/Earth-Day-Curriculum-Resources-Grades-K-5.html

http://www.nea.org/tools/lessons/Earth-Day-Curriculum-Resources-Grades-6-8.html

http://www.nea.org/tools/lessons/Earth-Day-Curriculum-Resources-Grade-9-12.html

#WWWay #WWEnergyBus #WWHomeBasedLearningPrep

We would like to recognize WHS sophomore Hannah Walters for donating her FFA show rabbits to serve as therapy pets to Truecare Living Center. 🐇🐇🐇

Since the Covid-19 Pandemic halted FFA livestock exhibitions across the nation, Hannah has prayed about what to do with her show animals. She will be introducing the rabbits to the Truecare residents, with the help of D.O.N. Wanda Lambright. She hopes they bring a little sunshine and joy each day, just as they did for her while raising them. ❤️

Hannah has a love for serving others and in the future, she aspires to work in the field of therapy services or counseling.

Due to potential difficulties acquiring enough products (bread, milk, produce) to provide multiple meals on a single day, along with other constraints, Westwood ISD will resume the previous practice of serving curbside meals and delivering meals daily Monday-Friday.

This change will begin on Tuesday, April 14, since meals have been provided through Monday, April 13th. The time and location will remain the same, curbside pick up at the high school from 10:00 am to 12:00 pm. Westwood will continue to deliver to your home address for those who need this. We ask for you to leave a box outside your residence if you are able, to limit contact with those delivering the meals.

Thank you for your support.

It's SELF CARE SUNDAY!! What are you doing to take care of yourself both physically AND mentally?? Mrs. Coates has some ideas for you:

1. Meditate
2. Sing
3. Be Still

What a great way to bring the same Energy Bus principles taught at Westwood ISD to your home! We can all benefit from positive energy, especially during these concerning times. Thank you, Energy Bus for Schools Leadership Journey for this excellent tool.

The Energy Bus for Schools Leadership Journey

We are excited to offer FREE Student Workshops (K-12)! We will support students as they look for opportunities in challenges as they seek ways to stay positive during their time away from school! Sign your child up today - more workshops coming soon!!

Dear Westwood Primary Family,
We hope you all are well. Our teachers will be working this next week on assembling learning activities for each grade level. We will have these available electronically on the district webpage and paper copies available for pick up. The pick-up dates for the learning bags are March 31st, April 7th, and April 14th from 10:00 am to 12:00 pm. We will have tables set up outside and bring these to your cars.

Querida familia primaria de Westwood,
Esperamos que todos estén bien. Nuestros maestros trabajarán esta próxima semana en el montaje de actividades de aprendizaje para cada nivel de grado. Tendremos estos disponibles electrónicamente en la página web del distrito y copias en papel disponibles para su recogida. Las fechas de recogida de las bolsas de aprendizaje son el 31 de marzo, el 7 de abril y el 14 de abril de 10:00 am a 12:00 pm. Tendremos mesas afuera y las llevaremos a sus coches.

Westwood ISD update:

The District will continually monitor the developments of the COVID-19 (coronavirus) and will provide an update on the suspension of normal school activities no later than Noon on April 17.

The District will provide additional information concerning student meals by Noon on Friday, March 20.

The District will provide additional information concerning Home-Learning by Noon on Friday, March 20.

All updates will be provided via all District social media accounts and the District website.

Westwood ISD Long-Range Instructional and Facilities Steering Committee

At 6pm on March 10th and 12th in the High School cafeteria, Westwood Independent School District will be holding two informational meetings about the establishment of a steering committee that will be responsible for the development of a long-range instructional and facilities master plan.

Participation in the steering committee will require attendance in the first meeting of the Long-Range Steering Committee that will be held in High School cafeteria at 6:00pm on March 24th.

In Mr. Hanna's Art I class, students learned about Black History Month and why we celebrate the achievements of African Americans in US history. Students picked a prominent African American figure and wrote a short bio about that person. They then constructed a shadow box and used their reports as the background, cut out a picture of that person and drew an image that represents what the individual was known for. Stop in the 300 building and see a short glimpses into these awesome individuals' lives.

An online survey will be available from February 10-21 on the district’s website, www.westwoodisd.net. If you do not have access to a computer, one will be available during the same period at the Administration Building, 4524 W. Oak

post_text:
⭐️⭐️ Westwood Scores a Perfect 100 ⭐️⭐️

The 2018-2019 financial accountability scores are in - and Westwood ISD scores a 100 - again!

Under the Texas Education Agency’s (TEA) rating system, Westwood ISD earned a score that gives the school an A and the designation of Financially Superior.

The TEA Financial Integrity Rating System of Texas (FIRST) rates school districts based on financial accountability, audit results, and money management throughout a certain school year. According to TEA, “The system is designed to encourage Texas public schools to better manage their financial resources to provide the maximum allocation possible for direct instructional purposes.”

Westwood ISD continues the Financially Superior Rating streak started in the 2002-2003 school year!
